<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=BRIC&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Elder, Miriam, and Leahy, Joe, et al., <a href="http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/d31392b2-89ca-11dd-8371-0000779fd18c.html?nclick_check=1" class="external text" title="http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/d31392b2-89ca-11dd-8371-0000779fd18c.html?nclick_check=1" rel="nofollow"><i>Who’s who: Bric leaders take their place at the top table</i></a>, Financial Times, London, September 25, 2008</li>
<li>O'Neill, Jim, <a href="http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/0dcb6f1c-8906-11dd-a179-0000779fd18c.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/0dcb6f1c-8906-11dd-a179-0000779fd18c.html" rel="nofollow"><i>BRICs could point the way out of the Economic Mire</i></a>, Financial Times, London, September 23, 2008, p.28.</li>
<li>Mark Kobayashi-Hillary, 'Building a Future with BRICs: The Next Decade for Offshoring' (Nov 2007). <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9783540464532" class="internal">ISBN 978-3-540-46453-2</a>.</li>
</ul>
